UN Secretary General Ban Ki-moon on Wednesday voiced outrage at deadly bombings in the Indian city of Jaipur.
Indian police on Wednesday arrested two men after eight near-simultaneous bombings killed 63 people and wounded 216 in the Rajasthan tourist city of Jaipur, the state's chief minister said.
Japan on Wednesday condemned the bomb blasts in the Indian city of Jaipur that killed at least 80 people, saying the attack was "unforgivable."
Afghan President Hamid Karzai condemned Wednesday bombings that killed about 80 people in the Indian city of Jaipur, saying the killing of innocents was justified by no religion or culture.
A previously unknown Islamic militant group claimed Thursday to have carried out deadly bombings in the historic Indian city of Jaipur by planting bicycles packed with explosives on the city's crowded streets, police said.
